{
  "stem": "2170.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But, you have to come back until everything-- you have to-- we just opened the embassy.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And you have to have, we have to have all typed and everything.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And then you'll have the passport, and you'll go to America.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I came back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "They made for me a Polish passport.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And I, with the passport, I went back to the American embassy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "When I came to the American embassy, it was in the-- like in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And I had the passport and I told-- and I saw [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Barisivna ?], secretary.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "First what she did, she called all the workers in the embassy, the secretaries, the assistants, to fingerprint me, to put on affidavits right the way that I have to go to the KGB.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And also a letter to the American attache, military attache in Odessa.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "As soon as there's going to be an American ship to transfer me to the United States.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And they made a party for me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "After that all of this, [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "Avril ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Herimon ?] was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "He congratulated me what I did, that nobody could believe that a boy like you could do that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And I came into Moscow with not the right papers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And I'm going to the KGB headquarters in Lubyanka to see the assistant of Beria.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "The second day.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And I come over there, big building, also not far from Red Square.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "I knew already where I'm running.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "Moscow was already like to me, like-- like I'm running around over here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Matter of fact, I was running so fast, when I came into the metro, I couldn't-- I was just jumping.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And the doors opened up, and I jumped at that big general with his big medals.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And I said, excuse me, I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
